name: Edwin M. BOSLER v. Mitchell SUGARMAN

parties: Edwin M. BOSLER v. Mitchell SUGARMAN.

opinions.text:
ORDER
This case came before the court on plaintiff’s motion pursuant to Rule 16(g) to affirm a judgment of the Superior Court entered by default against the defendant for failure to make discovery. After hearing the arguments of counsel, the motion to affirm is hereby denied.

attorneys: Temkin, Merolla & Zurier, Amedeo C. Merolla, Barry J. Kusinitz, Providence, for plaintiff.
Smith & Smith, Incorporated, Z. Hershel Smith, Providence, for defendant.

Smith & Smith, Incorporated, Z. Hershel Smith, Providence, for defendant.
